A Libyan man had a shock when he returned to his car after seeking shelter from shelling.

A live mortar shell had become wedged in the bodywork of the vehicle as it stood parked in the city of Benghazi.

Fawwaz Qasim Kassis risked his life to take the snap of the grenade, which struck the car on the hatch to the petrol tank.

